clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For adjunctive treatment of chronic simple open angle glaucoma secondary glaucoma and preoperatively in acute angle closure glaucoma where delay of surgery is desired in order to lower intraocular pressure

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Dichlorphenamide is an oral carbonic anhydrase inhibitor indicated for adjunctive treatment of chronic simple open angle glaucoma secondary glaucoma and preoperatively in acute angle closure glaucoma where delay of surgery is desired in order to lower intraocular pressure Carbonic anhydrase inhibitors reduce intraocular pressure by partially suppressing the secretion of aqueous humor inflow
